o.</us_distribution><global_distribution>Europe</global_distribution><global_distribution>Asia</global_distribution><global_distribution>introduced in South America</global_distribution><global_distribution>Australia.</global_distribution><discussion>Spergularia rubra was collected in 1901 on ballast in Alabama (Mohr, DS), the only record in the southeastern United States. It is the most widely distributed Spergularia species found outside of saline areas in the flora and has been in North America since at least the 1860s.</discussion></treatment>
